The UN agency based in the Netherlands has no power to adjudicate territory and has stipulated that it will not determine the outcome of any possible negotiations.
The fact that the International Court of Justice's resolution came only six months after the final arguments indicates that the case was "not complicated", said Chilean expert Paz Zárate.
