On Monday, Bolivia will offer Chile "an extraordinary opportunity to open a new era of relations" and the chance to "end 139 years of disagreements with mutual benefits", said.
Calzadilla also denied that Morales, who is still one of the most popular presidents in Latin America, was using the maritime issue as a political football.
