The new German warship, postponed again
The new German frigate was supposed to be commissioned in 2014 to replace the old Cold War-era ships, but it won't happen until at least next year due to defective systems and the increasing cost, local media reported.
The delivery of the "Rheinland-Pfalz", the ship that leads the new Baden-Württemberg class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to a report in the newspaper Die Zeit, which cites a military spokesman.
